    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-07-27T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-07-27T19:00:00-05:00" n="386"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d386">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">846E.2395/7–2751: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Ceylon</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d386fn1">Repeated for information to London as telegram
                        665.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-07-27T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 27, 1951—8 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 29 July 19. Second Secy Ceylon
                        Emb<note n="2" xml:id="d386fn2">G. S. Peiris.</note> brought <gloss
                        target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> reply July 25 re possible rubber contract.
                    Requested US send rep Ceylon or instruct US Emb Ceylon discuss contract with
                    rubber trade.<note n="3" xml:id="d386fn3">A memorandum of this conversation of
                        July. 25, not printed, is in file 846E.2395/7–2651.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Ceylon says it can not contract Ceylon trade even informally. US replied it most
                    inappropriate US approach Ceylon trade. US proposal not in form of contract
                    presentable trade. If US were interested in talks with trade, wld do so with US
                    trade.</p>
                <p>Dept told Ceylon Emb it wld consult within US Gov re possibility discussions
                    Ceylon Govt to Govt even though Ceylon had not indicated basis negot in which
                    interested.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_GSA1">GSA</gloss> agrees
                    ask you discuss contract with <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss>. Instructions
                    re US position on terms contract being prepared and will be forwarded next week.
                    Such instructions will also state <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> can itself
                    discuss with Ceylonese trade if it thinks desirable but such talks shld be most
                    discrete in order not disturb market.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
